Steps to create a repository in github.com.
sign in with login credentials
click on create new reposity(+)
give a name for repository.
download the repository to the host system using this command----git clone https://github.com/your_username/abc.git
then copy or add files to that repository/directory.
Now execute these commands to push the files to the github.
cd abc
git init
git add *
git commit -m "first commit"
git push -u origin master
--after this command it will ask your login credentials.

to go the github.com/your_username/abc.git and you will see the files you just added in the repository.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

to download the files to vm instances carry out these commands

git clone https://github.com/your_username/abc.git
cd abc-- go to abc directory
ls --- list all files and you should see the files you added to repository.


to upload the war file in tomcat7 server execute these commands

mv your_project.war file /var/lib/tomcat7/webapps

now restart the tomcat7 server using this command --- sudo service tomcat7 restart






